"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The parameter 'norm_hist' is set to False, which means the histogram will show counts instead of density. However, the seaborn documentation states that if a KDE (Kernel Density Estimate) or fitted density is plotted, the histogram height should show density rather than count. Since the default behavior of distplot is to include a KDE, setting 'norm_hist' to False is incorrect.\",\n  \"patch\": \"5c5\\n< sns.distplot(data.tip, norm_hist=False)\\n---\\n> sns.distplot(data.tip, norm_hist=True)\"\n}"